    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Kristóf Batthyány (Prague, 21 January 1544)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Oláh has understood from Batthyány's letter what he wants him to do: if
                            the King sends him as a legate or on some other official trip, Oláh
                            should promote Battyhány’s affairs alongside the ruler. Now the King is
                            sending Battyhány to Zagreb, to the Slavonian assembly. Oláh asks
                            Battyhány to promote the recovery of both the possessions of Oláh’s
                            friends and his own tithe, as the King has ordered. The King has not
                            responded to the letter regarding Batthyány’s payment, but Oláh will be
                            on it. The King says about donating Gyulai’s estates that this cannot be
                            done while Gyulai’s son is alive; so Oláh now turns to Batthyány,
                            thinking that the King will listen to the servitors’ advice once Gyulai
                            dies.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Salutem plurimam et mei commendationem, Magnifice Domine et Amice
                        Honorandissime!<note type="critic">Kristóf Batthyány (†1571) was Royal
                        Grand-cup-bearer from 1534 until his death, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Fallenbüchl</hi> 1988, 91.</note></p>
                <p>Ex litteris<note type="critic">We do not know this letter.</note>
                    Dominationis Vestrae Magnificae mihi redditis intellexi, quibus in rebus meam
                    desideret operam. Si quae res et occasio occurrerit, in qua Dominatio Vestra
                        <persName>suae maiestati</persName><note type="critic">King Ferdinand
                        I.</note> servire possit, sive in legatione obeunda, sive in aliis negotiis
                    curandis, ego ero apud maiestatem suam regiam, dominum nostrum clementissimum
                    sollicitator Dominationis Vestrae Magnificae. Maiestas sua hanc eiusdem
                    oblationem serviendi clementer et audivit et accepit. Nunc sua maiestas
                    Dominationem Vestram ad conventum Sclavonium <placeName>Zagrabis</placeName>
                    celebrandum designavit. Quam rogo, velit ibi bonis meis amicis et promotor esse
                    in decimis meis restituendis, sicuti maiestas sua mandavit. <choice>
                        <orig>De litteris</orig>
                        <supplied>Ad litteras</supplied>
                    </choice> ad <persName>Albertum praepositum</persName><note type="critic">Albert
                        Peregi.</note> pro restitutione salarii dandas nondum sua maiestas
                    respondit, ego tamen suam maiestatem sollicitabo. De bonis
                        <persName>Gywlai</persName><note type="critic">István Gyulai was <hi
                            rend="italic">viceispán</hi> of Varasd county and a retainer <hi
                            rend="italic">(familiaris)</hi> of the Batthyány family. See <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Terbe</hi> 2010, 60, and 66.</note>
                    <del corresp="Olahus">petendis</del> Dominationi Vestrae Magnificae dandis
                    respondit sua maiestas, quod interea, dum vivit adhuc filius illius unus,<note
                        type="critic">János Gyulai (†1567), Ferenc Batthyány became his
                        guardian.</note>
                <milestone unit="pb"/> non potest cuipiam conferre bona illius legitime. Advertar igitur
                    Dominationem Vestram de illius vivi adhuc filii vel morte, vel vita, et
                    quamprimum eius exitum significet, maiestatem suam arbitror rationem servitiorum
                    Dominationi Vestrae habituram. Ego vero in his, quibus a me fieri poterit, ero
                    sincerus amicus et servitor Dominationis Vestrae, quae valeat feliciter, et me
                    habeat commendatum.</p>
                <p>Ex <placeName>Praga</placeName>
                    <del corresp="Olahus">11</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">21</add>.
                    Ianuarii anno 1544.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">Vester Nicolaus Olahus episcopus Zagrabiensis etc. sua
                        manu</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Magnifico domino Christophori de Bathyan pincernarum regalium
                    magistro, et consiliario regio etc. domino et amico honorandissimo.</p>
            </div>
